W-Navigation-Pivot — DONE — 2026-05-01

SPEC §0 navigation model + Day/Night lobby chooser landed. Three commits.

Files touched:
  index.html
    - CSS: body.in-stage hides #nav-bar, #top-strip, resets #hunt-hud inset to 0
    - CSS: .back-btn pill (top-left of HUD, pointer-events:auto)
    - DOM: #hunt-back-btn ("← MENU") added inside #hunt-hud
  js/wg-game.js
    - module-state: currentLevelMode = 'day' (persists across re-renders of stage select)
    - buildHuntRuntime(stageId, mode): writes rt.mode ('day' | 'night')
    - startHunt(stageId, mode): adds body.in-stage; emits hunt:stage-start with mode
    - exitHunt(): removes body.in-stage; restores tabs + stage list
    - setupNav(): wires #hunt-back-btn → exitHunt()
    - showHuntStageList(): replaced flat 18-card list with [DAY | NIGHT] mode tabs
      atop a 2-col grid of 18 cards. Day cards = warm green tint;
      Night cards = deep blue tint + ☾ icon. All stages unlocked for now.

Manual verification (preview server localhost:3996):
  - Lobby: nav-bar + top-strip + 18 cards visible. Day/Night tabs render.
  - Click NIGHT MODE → cards re-tint to deep blue, STAGE labels show ☾.
  - Tap STAGE 1 card on NIGHT MODE → runtime.mode = 'night', stage 1 active.
  - body.className === 'in-stage'. nav-bar display:none. top-strip display:none.
  - hunt-back-btn visible, hunt-stage-select removed.
  - Click ← MENU → runtime cleared, body.in-stage removed, nav + top-strip restored,
    stage-select recreated with 18 cards.
  - No console errors.

Downstream: hunt-waves / hunt-render / hunt-torch (Night Mode mechanics from
SPEC §0) read rt.mode === 'night' to apply enemy density, hidden bosses,
torch-radius dimming. This worker only stores the value; downstream workers
implement the gameplay differences.

Known soft notes (not blocking):
  - HuntTutorial.maybeStart still fires on Stage 1 entry — covers the screen
    once on first run; existing behavior, not in this worker's scope.
  - The "highest unlocked" gating was removed per worker spec ("all 18 stages
    can be unlocked"). State.huntProgress.highestUnlocked is still updated
    by results.js for future use.
